Maven Basics 

What is Maven ?
It is a build and dependency management tool . Also it can be reffered to as " Project Management Tool " .

Why Maven ?
    • Common Interface .
    • mvn clean install .
    • It can manage dependencies such as Jar files , servlets .
    • Repository is used .
    • Can be reused .

How To Create A Maven Project ?
* To create a a maven project in cmd line we use " mvn install " command .
* To create a maven project in eclipse , we simply create a new file and then select 
" Maven Project " .

Commands Used In Maven Are :
    • mvn clean : This command cleans the maven project by deleting the target directory .
    • mvn compile : This command compiles the java source classes of the maven project .
    • mvn install : This command builds the maven project and installs the project files (JAR, WAR, pom.xml, etc) to the local repository.
    • mvn deploy : This command is used to deploy the artifact to the remote repository.
    • mvn package : This command builds the maven project and packages them into a JAR, WAR, etc.

Maven Life Cycle Phases  : 
A Maven phase represents a stage in the Maven build lifecycle. Each phase is responsible for a specific task.
Here are some of the most important phases in the default build lifecycle :
    • validate: check if all information necessary for the build is available
    • compile: compile the source code
    • test-compile: compile the test source code
    • test: run unit tests
    • package: package compiled source code into the distributable format (jar, war )
    • integration-test: process and deploy the package if needed to run integration tests
    • install: install the package to a local repository
    • deploy: copy the package to the remote repository


